<span key="33c8dc83b45d4837a83d1086e69d5ce9"><span offset-key="33c8dc83b45d4837a83d1086e69d5ce9:0">Fluency on the command line is a skill often neglected or considered arcane, but it improves your flexibility and productivity as an engineer in both obvious and subtle ways. This is a selection of notes and tips on using the command-line that we’ve found useful when working on Linux. Some tips are elementary, and some are fairly specific, sophisticated, or obscure. This page is not long, but if you can use and recall all the items here, you know a lot.</span></span>

<span key="5af06f0a77d742b9ae36935645fcfd42"><span offset-key="5af06f0a77d742b9ae36935645fcfd42:0">Awesome-Selfhosted</span></span>

<span key="dfe75b785dba44068e79141b459945a3"><span offset-key="dfe75b785dba44068e79141b459945a3:0">This is a list of </span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_software" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="e68cc947b28741d481d3fb1ea6163e57" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="107c401aec714d6083a263caf305fd6b"><span data-offset-key="107c401aec714d6083a263caf305fd6b:0">Free</span></span></span></a><span key="e5dd056a3bb44929b0a1b6ce563481e2"><span offset-key="e5dd056a3bb44929b0a1b6ce563481e2:0"> Software </span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_service" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="9fac310ee1bc4d05a8b9833266ed4329" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="1035d8348ce4445c8c99f2c48e3e8724"><span data-offset-key="1035d8348ce4445c8c99f2c48e3e8724:0">network services</span></span></span></a><span key="04523c0055fa4c2da3c506f9c4df3531"><span offset-key="04523c0055fa4c2da3c506f9c4df3531:0"> and </span></span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_application" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="d9f0860904cd4424aa33fd399f672b41" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="45716f3503f94745be51941108dbd4e1"><span data-offset-key="45716f3503f94745be51941108dbd4e1:0">web applications</span></span></span></a><span key="70859fe95a6f40dbb0a51d7ff8e95af2"><span offset-key="70859fe95a6f40dbb0a51d7ff8e95af2:0"> which can be hosted locally. Non-Free software is listed on the </span></span><a href="https://github.com/awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted/blob/master/non-free.md" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="66e9690cf5a446a3bda14dc487ae3d8e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="9cd6e2dfd3764e29aeee310409900c41"><span data-offset-key="9cd6e2dfd3764e29aeee310409900c41:0">Non-Free</span></span></span></a><span key="d9bcb138489e4ff0b3d86f9baedfee17"><span offset-key="d9bcb138489e4ff0b3d86f9baedfee17:0"> page.</span></span>

## 

<span key="7668e35c6cf74de5895b9178f559291f"><span offset-key="7668e35c6cf74de5895b9178f559291f:0">ripienaar/free-for-dev</span></span>

## 

<span key="37ebc8787adb4531a737bc42abb052a6"><span offset-key="37ebc8787adb4531a737bc42abb052a6:0">free-for.dev</span></span>

<span key="573a958993d5497da365fb477a620329"><span offset-key="573a958993d5497da365fb477a620329:0">Developers and Open Source authors now have a massive amount of services offering free tiers, but it can be hard to find them all to make informed decisions.</span></span>

<span key="fafee81526d847ffbe2f56a4604222b7"><span offset-key="fafee81526d847ffbe2f56a4604222b7:0">This is a list of software (SaaS, PaaS, IaaS, etc.) and other offerings that have free tiers for developers.</span></span>

<span key="8af64745102749fe86e973c044b7cc9b"><span offset-key="8af64745102749fe86e973c044b7cc9b:0">The scope of this particular list is limited to things that infrastructure developers (System Administrator, DevOps Practitioners, etc.) are likely to find useful. We love all the free services out there, but it would be good to keep it on topic. It’s a bit of a grey line at times so this is a bit opinionated; do not be offended if I do not accept your contribution.</span></span>

<span key="725d2f8311c94d868ae3f3df4ca0c36b"><span offset-key="725d2f8311c94d868ae3f3df4ca0c36b:0">This list is the result of Pull Requests, reviews, ideas and work done by 900+ people. You too can help by sending </span></span><a href="https://github.com/ripienaar/free-for-dev" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="5f648369e65f4f0b823831d2965412b6" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="32cd3813a3b044aca750998b740a2d58"><span data-offset-key="32cd3813a3b044aca750998b740a2d58:0">Pull Requests</span></span></span></a><span key="2182345d11124be3bc62678593f6283b"><span offset-key="2182345d11124be3bc62678593f6283b:0"> to add more services or by remove ones whose offerings have changed or been retired.</span></span>

<span key="ab7d37eb711549debc0da103fb7942e7">*NOTE:*<span offset-key="ab7d37eb711549debc0da103fb7942e7:1"> This list is only for as-a-Service offerings, not for self-hosted software. For a service to be eligible it has to offer a free tier and not just a free trial. If the free tier is time-bucketed it has to be for at least a year. We also consider the free tier from a security perspective, so SSO is fine but I will not accept services that restrict TLS to paid-only tiers.</span></span>

<span key="9499c203d20241ecb8dad9e1a40cd30a"><span offset-key="9499c203d20241ecb8dad9e1a40cd30a:0">### See how the exact same Medium.com clone (called </span></span><a href="https://demo.realworld.io" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c75c884d44984abcaf58f99afef9e298" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="0d308b8baad44b6fa3dd7a10294e9436"><span data-offset-key="0d308b8baad44b6fa3dd7a10294e9436:0">Conduit</span></span></span></a><span key="3e2299722c79440fb050d9031f178cae"><span offset-key="3e2299722c79440fb050d9031f178cae:0">) is built using different </span></span><a href="https://codebase.show/projects/realworld?category=frontend" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="222d8dfbada947dea90f7e06ff4f1900" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="cf42cd9f61844449a402a2da9541029b"><span data-offset-key="cf42cd9f61844449a402a2da9541029b:0">frontends</span></span></span></a><span key="b1410ddac7e94db5a9956a64a9e7bb4d"><span offset-key="b1410ddac7e94db5a9956a64a9e7bb4d:0"> and </span></span><a href="https://codebase.show/projects/realworld?category=backend" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="06b17df6222b49b78dccf092d8c3d2db" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="9876f2ac28554d4b91b89df39b85a7c2"><span data-offset-key="9876f2ac28554d4b91b89df39b85a7c2:0">backends</span></span></span></a><span key="68a55676dc7c47789df561f1af44838d"><span offset-key="68a55676dc7c47789df561f1af44838d:0">. Yes, you can mix and match them, because they all adhere to the same </span></span><a href="https://github.com/gothinkster/realworld/blob/master/spec" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="a4264e2c75e9423da02b13e4437bee9d" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="adac2e7ff70f41678c1b0444f09ff594"><span data-offset-key="adac2e7ff70f41678c1b0444f09ff594:0">API spec</span></span></span></a><span key="3b83f75c63d3403da0ba947931adc319"><span offset-key="3b83f75c63d3403da0ba947931adc319:0"> 😮😎</span></span>

<span key="41529f150195441cb04db7bd0a4b6220"><span offset-key="41529f150195441cb04db7bd0a4b6220:0">While most “todo” demos provide an excellent cursory glance at a framework’s capabilities, they typically don’t convey the knowledge & perspective required to actually build </span>*real*<span offset-key="41529f150195441cb04db7bd0a4b6220:2"> applications with it.</span></span>

<span key="f7e35eafeacd4b07a7c8cf6d4d87475a"><span offset-key="f7e35eafeacd4b07a7c8cf6d4d87475a:0">RealWorld solves this by allowing you to choose any frontend (React, Angular 2, & more) and any backend (Node, Django, & more) and see how they power a real world, beautifully designed fullstack app called “</span></span><a href="https://demo.realworld.io" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="33620f22f60541709a65af82bdd3bd54" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="8aa1ccd6f6e14c5da168a576dcd63685"><span data-offset-key="8aa1ccd6f6e14c5da168a576dcd63685:0">Conduit</span></span></span></a><span key="673a4efe8c1c4552bf92adc1824f2a13"><span offset-key="673a4efe8c1c4552bf92adc1824f2a13:0">”.</span></span>

<span key="916bcc71e57347d48aa709cad6b9f6de"><span offset-key="916bcc71e57347d48aa709cad6b9f6de:0">Or you can </span></span><a href="https://github.com/gothinkster/realworld/discussions/categories/wip-implementations" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c443b8a21488462b85eb32a0b3938193" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-14282_259-14283-237__"><span data-key="370411f63fa940049fd8e33a14aeeaf3"><span data-offset-key="370411f63fa940049fd8e33a14aeeaf3:0">view upcoming implementations (WIPs)</span></span></span></a><span key="b4337eb05ed7468d9a3306d58caa3030"><span offset-key="b4337eb05ed7468d9a3306d58caa3030:0">.</span></span>

## 

<span key="82ab25cb90884c7caad7267305f747aa"><span offset-key="82ab25cb90884c7caad7267305f747aa:0">How do I get up & running?</span></span>

<span key="df6d78dd8b12407b914430b1bef06f60"><span offset-key="df6d78dd8b12407b914430b1bef06f60:0">Follow the instructions in the README of whatever frontend and/or backend repo’s you want to get up and running.</span></span>

## 

<span key="3e50440134b44dde81ef89327345ddc4"><span offset-key="3e50440134b44dde81ef89327345ddc4:0">How to use?</span></span>

<span key="1bdbcc0b9a7f41a29cd34886523e1494"><span offset-key="1bdbcc0b9a7f41a29cd34886523e1494:0">All items in the Front-End Checklist are required for the majority of the projects, but some elements can be omitted or are not essential (in the case of an administration web app, you may not need RSS feed for example). We choose to use 3 levels of flexibility:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="295a704a9dc24dbea1c9f6528130c354"><span offset-key="295a704a9dc24dbea1c9f6528130c354:0">means that the item is recommended but can be omitted in some particular situations.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="22915cddd92d471894834391d3743a48"><span offset-key="22915cddd92d471894834391d3743a48:0">means that the item is highly recommended and can eventually be omitted in some really particular cases. Some elements, if omitted, can have bad repercussions in terms of performance or SEO.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="0ab9af1735fc4e2d9de09a5ac8788f89"><span offset-key="0ab9af1735fc4e2d9de09a5ac8788f89:0">means that the item can’t be omitted by any reason. You may cause a dysfunction in your page or have accessibility or SEO issues. The testing priority needs to be on these elements first.</span></span>

<span key="84ccc9c75eeb4de29d7be5099168017e"><span offset-key="84ccc9c75eeb4de29d7be5099168017e:0">Some resources possess an emoticon to help you understand which type of content / help you may find on the checklist:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="c02d42247d3342caad1056679c45df51"><span offset-key="c02d42247d3342caad1056679c45df51:0">📖: documentation or article</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="bc2edc9ec82648aebf65690d3663e28f"><span offset-key="bc2edc9ec82648aebf65690d3663e28f:0">🛠: online tool / testing tool</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="89525540b15f47e09950746030d5cc41"><span offset-key="89525540b15f47e09950746030d5cc41:0">📹: media or video content</span></span>
